   2035          /***************************************************************************//**
   2036           * Retrieves the absolute retained-banks mask for the memory type of the given heap.
   2037           *
   2038           * The heap is used only to select which retention control (memory type, e.g. DMEM,
   2039           * DTCM) to query. The returned mask is an absolute bitmap over all banks in that
   2040           * retention control (bank indices 0 to num_banks-1). It includes both banks that
   2041           * belong to this heap's region and banks outside this heap's region that are in
   2042           * the same memory type. So the mask aggregates retention across the entire
   2043           * memory type, not just this heap.
   2044           *
   2045           * Returns 0 when disabled or on error (e.g. NULL heap). UINT64_MAX is not used
   2046           * for error because it is a valid mask meaning all banks retained; 0 is not a
   2047           * valid mask because BSS/data and other fixed allocations always retain some banks.
   2048           ******************************************************************************/

   \                                 In section .text, align 2, keep-with-next
   2049          uint64_t sl_memory_heap_get_absolute_retained_banks_mask(const sl_memory_heap_t *heap)
   2050          {
